725488f-a.title: Queens: 57th Road - 61st Street
725488f-a.text:
57th Road, west of 6lst Street (right not shown), showing a rear
view of homes facing on Maspeth Ave. The low 12 story structure on
the left is No. 6051 Maspeth Ave., and is at the S.W. corner. Here, G.k.
Hyatt resided in 1852, opposite the Quaker Meeting House which was at the
S.E. corner (extreme richt and not shown) and at that date a schoolhouse,
having been discontinued as a place of worship in 1810. St. Stanislos
Roman Catholic Church was erected there. (In 1923.)
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

727369f-a.title: Queens: Maspeth Avenue - 61st Street
727369f-a.text:
Maspeth Ave., south side, east of 61st Street, showing in the
foreground the two homes of Mrs. Winterson in 1873. The one in the
foreground was occupied by one Furman in 1873.
March 1923.
